content.description: Climb on the N side of the Dolphin. Nice, huge, sand-filled huecos provide a clean route to the top. Avoid the choss to the right of the route.
content.protection: the anchor on top of this boulder is expansion and should NOT be used for top roping this route- it was used for rappelling and cleaning the boulder in lieu of webbing- webbing can be used to create a TR anchor from a tree on the West side of the boulder, but you will need 100+ ft. to get the job done. The FA of this route was done rope less, just keep in mind that the quality of the rock is relatively poor if you choose to boulder this climb.
content.location: N side of dolphin. left side of wall.

content.description: A large Dolphin shaped rock very close to Acronym boulder on GSL trail. The Boulder is three sided, with moderate climbing on the N face, a steep, chossy project on the E facing side, and a difficult (potential BP) roof on the south face.
